  <fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[ f^{\sharp }_\bot  : \mathcal {O}_{X,x} \to  \mathcal {O}_{A,\bot } \cong  A, ]]></fr:tex>
  this induces a map <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\operatorname {Spec} A \to  \operatorname {Spec}\mathcal {O}_{X,x}]]></fr:tex> which indeed when post-composed with the inclusion <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\operatorname {Spec}\mathcal {O}_{X,x} \to  X]]></fr:tex> gives us <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[X]]></fr:tex>. This can be seen easily when <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[X]]></fr:tex> is affine, and the general case is trivial from the proof of <fr:link href="/schm-MWRT/" title="Affine scheme at a stalk" uri="https://charloced.github.io/schm-MWRT/" display-uri="schm-MWRT" type="local">Lemma <fr:contextual-number uri="https://charloced.github.io/schm-MWRT/" display-uri="schm-MWRT" /></fr:link>.
